title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\Rule
name: Rule
description:
A rule to be applied in a Policy.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.Rule

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.conditions
params.description: Additional restrictions that must be met. All conditions must pass for the rule to match.

params.name: data.ins
params.description: If one or more 'in' clauses are specified, the rule matches if the PRINCIPAL/AUTHORITY_SELECTOR is in at least one of these entries.

params.name: data.log_configs
params.description: The config returned to callers of tech.iam.IAM.CheckPolicy for any entries that match the LOG action.

params.name: data.not_ins
params.description: If one or more 'not_in' clauses are specified, the rule matches if the PRINCIPAL/AUTHORITY_SELECTOR is in none of the entries.

params.name: data.permissions
params.description: A permission is a string of form '..' (e.g., 'storage.buckets.list'). A value of '' matches all permissions, and a verb part of '' (e.g., 'storage.buckets.*') matches all verbs.
